This paper is primarily focused on the use of overparameterized deep neural networks for memorization and retrieval, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of associative memory, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization methods used in training the neural networks, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
